<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM29150 - Supplementary &amp; Defined terms: Information powers </h1>
<p>Paragraph 93 provides the authority for an officer of Revenue and Customs to request information from companies with approved SIPs and those who are submitting a SIP for approval.</p>
<p>For existing plans the notice to provide information will normally be in the form of an annual return (form 39). Paragraph 93 is the authority to include questions on the return relating to the liability for income tax or capital gains tax of any person who has participated in the plan; this will take the form of questions concerning awards and withdrawals of shares. </p>
<p>Paragraph 93 also provides the authority to request information about the administration of the SIP to confirm that the SIP has not been altered and still conforms to the relevant statutory requirements. In practice this is dealt with by the ongoing obligations of the company to seek prior approval from HMRC in specified circumstances (see <a href="ESSUM28350.htm">ESSUM28350</a>). There is no longer a requirement to provide information on the annual return in relation to plan alterations and constituent companies; however, the declaration on the annual return makes clear that </p>
<ul>
<li>any plan shares were eligible shares and must have been awarded to or acquired by participants in accordance with the approved plan</li>
<li>no alterations must have been made to key features of the plan without HMRCâ€™s approval</li>
</ul>
<p>Annual returns are normally issued on the first working day after the end of the tax year and the return should be received by HMRC (ESSU) within 3 months of the date of issue; penalties may be chargeable where the return is received late or is incomplete or inaccurate. For new SIPs being submitted for review and subsequent approval, paragraph 93 is the authority for requesting information necessary to determine whether the plan satisfies the relevant requirements of Schedule 2.</p>
<p>The information requested must only be that which the person to whom the notice (return) is addressed has or can reasonably obtain.</p>
